'''Francisco''' "'''Chico'''" '''Fernandes da Conceição''' ({{IPA|pt|fɾɐ̃ˈsiʃku kõsɐjˈsɐ̃w̃}}; born 14 December 2002) is a Portuguese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right winger]]  for [[Serie A]] club [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]].

Coming through Porto's youth system, Conceição was promoted to the first-team in 2021, winning a [[Double (association football)|domestic double]] of the Primeira Liga and [[Taça de Portugal]] in 2022. In July 2022, he moved to [[Eredivisie]] side [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], before returning to Porto in September 2023, on an initial one-year loan deal which was made permanent at the end of the season. He joined Juventus in August 2024 on an initial one-year loan deal which was made permanent at the end of the season.

Conceição is a former [[Portugal national youth football team|Portugal youth international]], representing his country at various youth levels, being part of [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21 team]]s that finished as runners-up in the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2021 European Under-21 Championship]]. He made his senior international debut in 2024, representing Portugal at the [[UEFA Euro 2024]], and went on to win the [[UEFA Nations League]] in [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|2025]].

==Club career==
=== Early career ===
Conceição was born in [[Coimbra]]. He started playing football at [[C.F. Os Belenenses|Belenenses]], due to his brothers Moisés and [[Rodrigo Conceição|Rodrigo]] also playing there, before moving to [[Sporting CP|Sporting]]'s academy in 2011 at the age of eight, spending six seasons at the club.<ref name="quem" /> With his father [[Sérgio Conceição|Sérgio]] becoming the manager of [[FC Porto|Porto]], he joined their academy and was subsequently loaned to their [[feeder club]] [[Padroense F.C.|Padroense]],<ref name="quem" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/2021/02/15/porto/francisco-conceicao-o-novo-abre-latas-do-fc-porto/noticia/226805/|title=Francisco Conceição, o novo "'abre-latas" do FC Porto|language=pt|trans-title=Francisco Conceição, FC Porto's new "can opener"|website=[[Rádio Renascença]]|author=Aresta, Luís|date=15 February 2021|accessdate=15 February 2021|archive-date=15 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215125628/https://rr.sapo.pt/2021/02/15/porto/francisco-conceicao-o-novo-abre-latas-do-fc-porto/noticia/226805/|url-status=live}}</ref> before fully joining Porto's youth setup in 2018.<ref name="quem" />

=== Porto ===
In August 2020, Conceição signed his first professional contract with the club until 2023,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/fc-porto/detalhe/francisco-conceicao-assina-contrato-profissional-com-o-fc-porto|title=Francisco Conceição assina contrato profissional com o FC Porto|language=pt|trans-title=Francisco Conceição signs professional contract with FC Porto|website=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|date=27 August 2020|accessdate=15 February 2021|archive-date=15 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215181932/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/fc-porto/detalhe/francisco-conceicao-assina-contrato-profissional-com-o-fc-porto|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/segunda-liga/artigos/filhos-de-sergio-conceicao-reforcam-equipa-b-do-fc-porto|title=Filhos de Sérgio Conceição reforçam equipa B do FC Porto|language=pt|trans-title=Sérgio Conceição's sons sign with Porto's B team|date=27 August 2020|accessdate=15 February 2021|website=Sapo Desporto|agency=[[Lusa News Agency|Lusa]]|archive-date=15 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215182545/https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/segunda-liga/artigos/filhos-de-sergio-conceicao-reforcam-equipa-b-do-fc-porto|url-status=live}}</ref> and made his professional debut for (Porto B) in a 1–0 loss against [[Varzim S.C.|Varzim]] during the [[2020–21 Liga Portugal 2]] season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1583112/varzim-vence-fc-porto-b-com-golo-solitario-de-yusuf|title=Varzim vence FC Porto B com golo solitário de Yusuf|language=pt|trans-title=Varzim wins against FC Porto B with solo Yusuf goal|date=13 September 2020|accessdate=15 February 2021|website=Notícias ao Minuto|agency=[[Lusa News Agency|Lusa]]|archive-date=15 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210515015807/https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1583112/varzim-vence-fc-porto-b-com-golo-solitario-de-yusuf|url-status=live}}</ref> On 15 January 2021, his father called Conceição for Porto's league match against [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] to replace [[Otávio (footballer, born 1995)|Otávio]], which ended 1–1. He made his debut in the Portuguese top tier in a 2–2 draw against [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] in the ''Derby da Invicta'', on 13 February 2021;<ref name="quem">{{cite web|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/quem-e-francisco-conceicao-alem-de-ser-filho-de-sergio-13352545.html|title=Quem é Francisco Conceição (além de ser filho de Sérgio)?|trans-title=Who is Francisco Conceição (besides being Sérgio's son)?|language=pt|date=14 February 2021|website=[[Diário de Notícias]]|author=Almeida, Isaura|accessdate=15 February 2021|archive-date=15 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215150539/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/quem-e-francisco-conceicao-alem-de-ser-filho-de-sergio-13352545.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://observador.pt/2021/02/13/francisco-so-ele-merecia-que-as-lagrimas-de-alegria-nao-tivessem-sido-em-vao-a-cronica-do-fc-porto-boavista/|title=Francisco, só ele, merecia que as lágrimas de alegria não tivessem sido em vão (a crónica do FC Porto-Boavista)|trans-title=Francisco, only him, deserved that the tears of joy wouldn't be for nothing (the chronicle of FC Porto-Boavista)|language=pt|date=13 February 2021|website=Observador|author=Fernandes, Mariana|accessdate=15 February 2021|archive-date=15 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215161704/https://observador.pt/2021/02/13/francisco-so-ele-merecia-que-as-lagrimas-de-alegria-nao-tivessem-sido-em-vao-a-cronica-do-fc-porto-boavista/|url-status=live}}</ref> with 13 minutes left and Porto trailing 2–1, within five minutes he won a penalty, which was by [[Sérgio Oliveira]], before scoring a goal that was ruled out by [[Video assistant referee|VAR]]. Four days later, he became the second youngest Porto player to feature in a [[UEFA Champions League]] match, coming on in the last minutes of a 2–1 win against [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] in the round of 16 of the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League|2020–21]] season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/francisco-conceicao-porto-manager-son-messi-comparisons/16e6u8tfn4qgc1pdtfyub8zkoi|title=Francisco Conceicao: Porto manager's son earning Messi comparisons|publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|access-date=12 July 2024|date=25 May 2021}}</ref> At the end of the month, he was fully promoted to the first-team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/2021/02/18/porto/francisco-conceicao-e-o-segundo-mais-jovem-de-sempre-a-estrear-se-na-champions-pelo-fc-porto/noticia/227190/|title=Francisco Conceição é o segundo mais jovem de sempre a estrear-se na Champions pelo FC Porto|trans-title=Francisco Conceição is the second youngest ever to debut in the Champions League for FC Porto|language=pt|date=18 February 2021|website=Rádio Renascença|accessdate=18 February 2021|archive-date=19 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210219190355/https://rr.sapo.pt/2021/02/18/porto/francisco-conceicao-e-o-segundo-mais-jovem-de-sempre-a-estrear-se-na-champions-pelo-fc-porto/noticia/227190/|url-status=live}}</ref>

In [[2021–22 FC Porto season|2021–22]], Conceição played 33 total games as Porto won a [[2021–22 Primeira Liga|league]] and [[2021–22 Taça de Portugal|cup]] [[Double (association football)|double]]; only four were starts, including one in the league.<ref name="double">{{cite news |title=Francisco Conceição nas redes sociais: "Sempre especial voltar às origens"|trans-title=Francisco Conceição on social networks: "It's always special to return to your roots"|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/porto/noticias/francisco-conceicao-nas-redes-sociais-sempre-especial-voltar-as-origens-15033971.html |access-date=21 July 2022 |work=[[O Jogo]] |date=20 July 2022 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He contributed three goals, beginning with a penalty to conclude a 5–1 home win over [[C.D. Feirense|Feirense]] in the fourth round of the [[Taça de Portugal]];<ref>{{cite news |title=FC Porto goleia Feirense e filho de Conceição estreia-se a marcar |trans-title=FC Porto thrash Feirense and Conceição's son scores for the first time |url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/fc-porto-goleia-feirense-e-filho-de-conceicao-estreia-se-a-marcar-14338071.html |access-date=21 July 2022 |work=Diário de Notícias |date=20 November 2021 |language=Portuguese |archive-date=18 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220518043812/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/fc-porto-goleia-feirense-e-filho-de-conceicao-estreia-se-a-marcar-14338071.html |url-status=live }}</ref> his first league goal on 8 January won the game 3–2 at [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]] two minutes after coming on for [[Fábio Cardoso]], causing his dad to celebrate wildly.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Coelho |first1=Nuno |title=Super-Díaz conduz dragões e Conceições dão o xeque-mate |trans-title=Super-Díaz drives the Dragons and the Conceiçãos do the checkmate |url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/fc-porto-consegue-reviravolta-no-estoril-e-e-lider-isolado-da-i-liga-14473733.html |access-date=21 July 2022 |work=Diário de Notícias |date=8 January 2022 |language=Portuguese |archive-date=28 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220528171835/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/fc-porto-consegue-reviravolta-no-estoril-e-e-lider-isolado-da-i-liga-14473733.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Porto Manager Brings On 19-Year-Old Son In 87th Minute. He Scores Game-Winner In The 89th |url=https://the18.com/soccer-entertainment/porto-manager-son-sergio-francisco-conceicao-goal |access-date=2024-06-19 |website=The18 |archive-date=19 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240619161522/https://the18.com/soccer-entertainment/porto-manager-son-sergio-francisco-conceicao-goal |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=O'Callaghan |first=Rory |date=2022-01-09 |title=Porto Manager Sergio Conceicao Celebrates Wildly After His Son Scores Dramatic Late Winner Off The Bench |url=https://www.sportbible.com/football/porto-manager-sergio-conceicao-celebrates-after-son-scores-winner-20220109 |access-date=2024-06-19 |website=SPORTbible |language=en |archive-date=20 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620233913/https://www.sportbible.com/football/porto-manager-sergio-conceicao-celebrates-after-son-scores-winner-20220109 |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Ajax ===
[[File:GAE - Ajax - 52788521318 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Conceição playing for [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] in 2023]]
On 21 July 2022, Conceição signed with [[Eredivisie]] club [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], on a five-year contract, with Ajax triggering Conceição's release clause.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ajax sign Francisco Conceição |url=https://english.ajax.nl/articles/ajax-sign-francisco-conceicao/ |access-date=2022-07-21 |website=english.ajax.nl |archive-date=21 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220721184634/https://english.ajax.nl/articles/ajax-sign-francisco-conceicao/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Nine days later, he was an unused substitute as they lost the [[2022 Johan Cruyff Shield]] 5–3 to [[PSV Eindhoven]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Supertaça para o PSV em partida de oito golos|trans-title=Super Cup for PSV in game of eight goals |url=https://rr.sapo.pt/bola-branca/noticia/futebol-internacional/2022/07/30/supertaca-para-o-psv-em-partida-de-oito-golos/294210/ |access-date=3 August 2022 |publisher=[[Rádio Renascença]] |date=30 July 2022 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He made his debut for [[Jong Ajax|the reserves]] on 8 August, equalising in a 1–1 [[Eerste Divisie]] draw at home to [[SC Telstar|Telstar]];<ref>{{cite news |last1=Brood |first1=Thomas |title=Met smaakmaker Conceição speelt Jong Ajax gelijk tegen Telstar |url=https://www.nhnieuws.nl/nieuws/307143/met-smaakmaker-conceicao-speelt-jong-ajax-gelijk-tegen-telstar |access-date=7 September 2022 |publisher=NH Nieuws |date=9 August 2022 |language=Dutch |archive-date=7 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220907215247/https://www.nhnieuws.nl/nieuws/307143/met-smaakmaker-conceicao-speelt-jong-ajax-gelijk-tegen-telstar |url-status=live }}</ref> his first-team debut came on 3 September in a 4–0 home win over [[SC Cambuur|Cambuur]], replacing double goalscorer [[Steven Bergwijn]] after 61 minutes.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Pus |first1=Milton |title=Dubbelslag Bergwijn helpt Ajax in het zadel tegen Cambuur na onrustige week |url=https://www.nhnieuws.nl/nieuws/308125/dubbelslag-bergwijn-helpt-ajax-in-het-zadel-tegen-cambuur-na-onrustige-week |access-date=7 September 2022 |publisher=NH Nieuws |date=4 September 2022 |language=Dutch |archive-date=20 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620233923/https://www.nhnieuws.nl/nieuws/308125/dubbelslag-bergwijn-helpt-ajax-in-het-zadel-tegen-cambuur-na-onrustige-week |url-status=live }}</ref>

Shortly after, Ajax manager [[Alfred Schreuder]] revealed that he intended to have Conceição behind [[Antony (footballer, born 2000)|Antony]] in the pecking order, in order for him to get used to his new team, but despite Antony's departure Conceição status within the team didn't change and he remained a substitute, after [[Mohammed Kudus]] was preferred as the club's starting right winger. Conceição also struggled because he could not speak Dutch or English, leading him to play on the second team to adjust to the Dutch game.<ref>[https://www.ajaxshowtime.com/bijzaken-en-geruchten/schreuder-ziet-in-blind-option-voor-op-het-middenveld-zou-hij-heel-goed-kunnen Ajax manager about Conceição, July 2022] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230528173252/https://www.ajaxshowtime.com/bijzaken-en-geruchten/schreuder-ziet-in-blind-option-for-midfield-he-might-be-very-good |date=28 May 2023 }} ''AjaxShowtime'', July 23, 2022. [https://web.archive.org/web/20230528173252/https://www.ajaxshowtime.com/bijzaken-en-geruchten/schreuder-ziet-in-blind-option-for-midfield-he-might-be-very-good Archived] on May 28, 2023.</ref>

On 1 November, two minutes after replacing Bergwijn, he scored his first goal to conclude a 3–1 win at [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] in the [[UEFA Champions League]] group stage.<ref>{{cite news |title=Rangers' defeat by Ajax sets new low and seals Champions League misery |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/nov/01/rangers-ajax-champions-league-match-report |access-date=1 May 2023 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=1 November 2022 |archive-date=20 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620233921/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/nov/01/rangers-ajax-champions-league-match-report |url-status=live }}</ref> He played in the [[2023 KNVB Cup final]] against PSV, coming on in the 75th minute for [[Steven Berghuis]] as the game ended 1–1 and Ajax lost on penalties.<ref>{{cite news |title=PSV-Ajax: Fábio Silva bate penálti e conquista Taça a Francisco Conceição |trans-title=PSV-Ajax: Fábio Silva scores penalty and wins Cup against Francisco Conceição |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/psv-eindhoven/fabio-silva/psv-ajax-fabio-silva-bate-penalti-e-conquista-taca-a-francisco-conceicao |access-date=1 May 2023 |publisher=Mais Futebol |date=30 April 2023 |language=Portuguese |archive-date=1 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230501211614/https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/psv-eindhoven/fabio-silva/psv-ajax-fabio-silva-bate-penalti-e-conquista-taca-a-francisco-conceicao |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Return to Porto ===
{{quote box
| quote = "I thought it was the best thing for me, knowing that things hadn't gone so well at Ajax. I think there are always positive points to take away from an experience. It was a difficult time. I went out with the aim of showing what I'm worth, I couldn't do it, I thought about what was missing, it's always our fault. I tried to hold on to that, see what was missing and returned to FC Porto. It was the right decision [for me]."
| source = — Conceição on his return to Porto<ref>{{cite news|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/selecao/fc-porto/francisco-conceicao-regressar-ao-fc-porto-foi-a-decisao-certa|title=Francisco Conceição: "Regressar ao FC Porto foi a decisão certa"|website=PSG Talk|language=pt|date=18 March 2024|access-date=2 June 2024|archive-date=2 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240602020918/https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/selecao/fc-porto/francisco-conceicao-regressar-ao-fc-porto-foi-a-decisao-certa|url-status=live}}</ref>
| align = right
| width = 27%
}}
On 1 September 2023, FC Porto announced that Conceição would be returning to the club on a season-long [[Loan (sports)|loan]] from Ajax. He was handed the number 10 shirt, the same number he wore at the end of his previous spell with the ''Dragons''.<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 September 2023 |title=Francisco Conceição de volta a casa |trans-title=Francisco Conceição is back home |url=https://www.fcporto.pt/pt/noticias/20230901-pt-francisco-conceicao-de-volta-a-casa |access-date=3 September 2023 |publisher=FC Porto |language=pt-PT |archive-date=1 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230901222033/https://www.fcporto.pt/pt/noticias/20230901-pt-francisco-conceicao-de-volta-a-casa |url-status=live }}</ref> The deal reportedly included a €10 million option-to-buy, which would become mandatory if he played at least 45 minutes in 25 matches.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 September 2023 |title=Francisco Conceição no FC Porto: confira os detalhes do acordo de empréstimo |trans-title=Francisco Conceição to FC Porto: check the details of the loan deal |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/porto/noticias/francisco-conceicao-no-fc-porto-confira-os-detalhes-do-acordo-de-emprestimo-16956317.html |access-date=3 September 2023 |publisher=[[O Jogo]] |language=pt-PT}}</ref> His return was criticized by the club's fans, including Mayor of Porto [[Rui Moreira]], who was one of the person against his return.<ref name="Improved">{{Cite web |date=6 March 2024 |title=FC Porto: anda um génio à solta no Dragão |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/fc-porto-anda-um-genio-a-solta-no-dragao-2024030617323073531 |access-date=2 June 2024 |publisher=[[A Bola]] |language=pt-PT |archive-date=20 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620233932/https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/fc-porto-anda-um-genio-a-solta-no-dragao-2024030617323073531 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Despite the criticism, Conceição began proving his doubters wrong, impressing in Porto's 1–0 league loss home against [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]] on November 3, earning a spot in the starting eleven.<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 March 2024 |title=A campanha de Francisco Conceição |url=https://www.abola.pt/opinioes/noticias/a-campanha-de-francisco-conceicao-2024032912122779352 |access-date=2 June 2023 |publisher=[[A Bola]] |language=pt-PT |archive-date=30 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240330174343/https://www.abola.pt/opinioes/noticias/a-campanha-de-francisco-conceicao-2024032912122779352 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="Improved"/> On 11 November, in a 2–1 league victory away at [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]], he assisted the first goal and scored the second.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-11 |title=Onde um filho derrotou a mãe, Francisco deu a vitória ao pai. FC Porto ganha em Guimarães |trans-title=Where a son defeated his mother, Francisco gave his father the victory. FC Porto wins in Guimarães |url=https://www.tsf.pt/desporto/vitoria-sc-fc-porto-relato-tsf-direto-i-liga-17310598.html |access-date=2023-11-11 |website=TSF Rádio Notícias |language=pt-PT |archive-date=20 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620233924/https://www.tsf.pt/desporto/vitoria-sc-fc-porto-relato-tsf-direto-i-liga-17310598.html/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He also scored in the next league match away [[F.C. Famalicão|Famalicão]] in a 3–0.<ref name="Improved"/> A month later, he scored his first UEFA Champions League goal for Porto, in a 5–3 home victory over [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]], in the final match of the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group H|group stage]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 December 2023 |title=Champions só no Porto |trans-title=Champions only at Porto |url=https://www.fcporto.pt/pt/noticias/20231213-pt-champions-so-no-porto |access-date=13 December 2023 |publisher=FC Porto |language=pt-pt |archive-date=13 December 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231213223806/https://www.fcporto.pt/pt/noticias/20231213-pt-champions-so-no-porto |url-status=live }}</ref> In January 2024, Ajax, who was monitoring form, tried to get him back from his loan, however, Porto refused to negotiate with Ajax.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 March 2024 |title=Ajax tentou 'resgatar' Francisco Conceição, FC Porto não deixou |work=Notícias ao Minuto |url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/2523899/ajax-tentou-resgatar-francisco-conceicao-fc-porto-nao-deixou |access-date=2 June 2024 |publisher=Desporto ao Minuto |language=pt-pt |archive-date=2 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240602012701/https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/2523899/ajax-tentou-resgatar-francisco-conceicao-fc-porto-nao-deixou |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Francisco Conceição moves to FC Porto permanently |url=https://english.ajax.nl/articles/francisco-conceicao-moves-to-fc-porto-permanently |access-date=2024-06-19 |website=english.ajax.nl |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 3 March, Conceição impressed in Porto's 5–0 league victory over Benfica in ''[[O Clássico]]'', creating the play for Porto's second goal, which was scored by [[Galeno]].<ref name="Improved"/> During the month, he continued to impress with his form establishing himself as one of the best dribblers in the world by [[International Centre for Sports Studies]] (CIES), being considered second best behind [[Jérémy Doku]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 April 2024 |title=CIES: Francisco Conceição é o segundo melhor driblador do mundo |url=https://cnnportugal.iol.pt/cies/porto/cies-francisco-conceicao-e-o-segundo-melhor-driblador-do-mundo |access-date=2 June 2024 |publisher=[[CNN Portugal]] |language=pt-pt |archive-date=30 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240530175112/https://cnnportugal.iol.pt/cies/porto/cies-francisco-conceicao-e-o-segundo-melhor-driblador-do-mundo |url-status=live }}</ref> On 17 April, in the second leg of the semifinals of the [[2023–24 Taça de Portugal]], he scored and assisted in a 3–1 victory away at Vitória de Guimarães, to help Porto reach the [[2023–24 Taça de Portugal#Final|final]] of the competition.<ref name="Improved"/> On 23 April, FC Porto announced that they had re-signed Conceição on a permanent basis in a deal worth €10 million, on a five-year contract. He also retained 20% of a future transfer for himself.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/fc-porto/liga/oficial-fc-porto-contrata-francisco-conceicao-em-definitivo|title=OFICIAL: FC Porto contrata Francisco Conceição em definitivo|website=Maisfutebol|language=pt|date=23 April 2024|access-date=24 April 2024|archive-date=20 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620234430/https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/fc-porto/liga/oficial-fc-porto-contrata-francisco-conceicao-em-definitivo|url-status=live}}</ref> Despite an underwhelming season from Porto, in which the club finished in third place in the [[2023–24 Primeira Liga|Primeira Liga]], Conceição had his breakthrough, finishing the season with 16 goal involvements (eight goals and eight assists), with Porto winning the Taça de Portugal after a 2–1 defeat of Sporting in the [[2024 Taça de Portugal Final|final]] on 26 May.<ref name="Taça">{{cite web|url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/fc-porto/taca-de-portugal-sergio-conceicao-e-o-terceiro-treinador-a-vencer-quatro-finais_d1574481|title=Taça de Portugal. Sérgio Conceição é o terceiro treinador a vencer quatro finais|trans-title=Portugal Cup. Sérgio Conceição is the third manager to win four finals|publisher=Rádio e Televisão de Portugal|language=pt|date=26 May 2024|access-date=27 May 2024|archive-date=26 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240526222131/https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/fc-porto/taca-de-portugal-sergio-conceicao-e-o-terceiro-treinador-a-vencer-quatro-finais_d1574481|url-status=live}}</ref>

He missed the start of [[2024–25 FC Porto season|the new season]], due to injury issues, though it came amid reports that Conceição refused to play for his new manager [[Vítor Bruno (football manager)|Vítor Bruno]], following an altercation between him and his father and previous manager Sérgio. Despite his new manager denying that there were issues between them, Conceição began seeking a move away from the club, with [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] reaching a verbal agreement with him over personal terms.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jn.pt/6290008823/vitor-bruno-e-francisco-conceicao-tornou-se-num-tema-delicado-e-nao-devia/|title=Vítor Bruno e Francisco Conceição: "Tornou-se num tema delicado e não devia"|publisher=[[Jornal de Notícias]]|language=pt|date=2 August 2024|access-date=31 August 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dn.pt/8047616257/vitor-bruno-deixa-francisco-conceicao-fora-de-jogo-e-admite-sondagens/#error=login_required&state=b6a148f8-4c32-43a2-8592-c0c1c3cf0e57|title=Vítor Bruno deixa Francisco Conceição fora de jogo e admite sondagens|publisher=[[Diário de Notícias]]|language=pt|date=23 August 2024|access-date=31 August 2024}}</ref>

===Juventus===
On 27 August 2024, Conceição joined [[Serie A]] club Juventus on a season-long loan for €7 million, plus €3 million in add-ons, if Juventus qualifies to the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League]]. Both clubs also drafted a [[gentlemen's agreement]], where Juventus would have the priority to trigger his €30 million release clause in June 2025.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ufficiale {{!}} Francisco Conceição è un giocatore della Juventus |url=https://www.juventus.com/it/news/articoli/ufficiale-francisco-conceicao-e-un-giocatore-della-juventus |publisher=Juventus |access-date=27 August 2024 |language=Italian |date=27 August 2024 }}</ref> He was given the number 7 shirt, left vacant since the exit of [[Federico Chiesa]] the same month and previously worn by [[Portugal national football team|national team]] teammate [[Cristiano Ronaldo]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bolanarede.pt/especial-bola-na-rede/atualidade/francisco-conceicao-assume-a-camisola-7-da-juventus-que-foi-de-chiesa-e-cristiano-ronaldo/ |title=Francisco Conceição assume a camisola 7 da Juventus que foi de Chiesa e Cristiano Ronaldo |website=Bola Na Rede |date=31 August 2024 |access-date=31 August 2024}}</ref>

He made his debut for the club on 1 September, as a substitute in a 0–0 league draw against [[AS Roma|Roma]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/articles/juve-held-to-goalless-draw-in-tight-encounter-with-roma-01-09-2024|title=Juve held to goalless draw in tight encounter with Roma|date=1 September 2024|website=Juventus FC}}</ref> After missing the next matches due to an hamstring injury he suffered in training, Conceição made his return from injury on 28 September, scoring his first goal for the club in a 3–0 league win against [[Genoa CFC|Genoa]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://football-italia.net/juventus-confirm-conceicao-injury-recovery/ |title=Juventus confirm Conceiçao injury: recovery time revealed|website=Football Italia |date=5 September 2024 |access-date=28 September 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/serie-a-francisco-conceicao-estreia-se-a-marcar-em-vitoria-da-juventus-2024092817442985334|title=Serie A: Francisco Conceição estreia-se a marcar em vitória da Juventus|website=[[A Bola]]|date=28 September 2024 |access-date=28 September 2024}}</ref> On 2 October, he came on as a 12th-minute substitute, with his team being down to ten players, he assisted the equalizer and scored a last-minute winner in Juventus's 3–2 comeback victory at away to [[RB Leipzig]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|Champions League league phase]].<ref>{{cite web |date=2 October 2024 |title=Francisco Conceição salva Juventus, Real Madrid perde na Champions |url=https://www.publico.pt/2024/10/02/desporto/noticia/francisco-conceicao-salva-juventus-real-madrid-perde-champions-2106357 |access-date=4 October 2024 |website=[[Público (Portugal)|Público]]|language=pt}}</ref> On 18 June 2025, he scored a brace against [[Al Ain FC|Al-Ain FC]] in Juventus' opening match of the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Cup]].<ref>[https://www.sofascore.com/pt/football/match/al-ain-juventus/MdbsHQo#id:13200293 Al-Ain - Juventus], sofascore.com, retrieved 19 June 2025</ref>

On 22 July 2025, Juventus announced permanent signing of Conceição from Porto on a five-year deal worth €30.4 million, plus €1.6 million in potential bonuses.<ref>{{cite web |title=Francisco Conceicao signs a permanent deal |url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/articles/francisco-conceicao-signs-a-permanent-deal |publisher=Juventus FC |access-date=22 July 2025 |date=22 July 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Conceição represented [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] at [[Portugal national under-16 football team|under-16]], [[Portugal national under-17 football team|under-17]] and [[Portugal national under-18 football team|under-18 levels]], for a total of 15 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] and three goals. In March 2021, he took part in the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], earning his first [[Cap (sport)|cap]] for the [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21 side]], in a 1–0 victory in [[Croatia national under-21 football team|Croatia]] on 25 March. On 31 March, he became the youngest player (aged 18 years and 90 days) to score for Portugal in the [[UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], after closing the 3–0 victory against [[Switzerland national under-21 football team|Switzerland]] in their final match in the group phase.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://observador.pt/2021/03/31/francisco-conceicao-o-mais-novo-a-marcar-em-europeus-sub-21-deixa-me-muito-orgulhoso-mas-nao-penso-nisso/|title=Francisco Conceição, o mais novo a marcar em Europeus Sub-21: "Deixa-me muito orgulhoso mas não penso nisso"|publisher=Observador|date=31 March 2021|access-date=12 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/selecao/2032-portugal-2-0-switzerland-rui-jorge-s-side-cruise-into-u21-european-championship-quarter-finals|title=Portugal 3–0 Switzerland – Rui Jorge's side cruise into U21 European Championship quarter-finals|publisher=PortuGOAL|date=31 March 2021|access-date=16 July 2023}}</ref> He would help Portugal finish as runners-up, after losing in the final 1–0 to [[Germany national under-21 football team|Germany]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Highlights, report: Germany beat Portugal for third U21 EURO title|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/news/026a-127532d17acc-e079bf3c8a1c-1000--highlights-report-germany-beat-portugal-for-third-u21-euro-/|website=UEFA|date=6 June 2021|access-date=7 June 2021|archive-date=29 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221029031154/https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2031981--germany-vs-portugal/postmatch/report/|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2023, Conceição took part in the [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2036139--portugal-vs-belgium/|title=History: Portugal 2-1 Belgium &#124; UEFA Under-21 2023|website=UEFA|date=27 June 2023|access-date=18 June 2024|archive-date=14 January 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240114105538/https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2036139--portugal-vs-belgium/|url-status=live}}</ref> Portugal were eliminated from the tournament, on 2 July, after a 1–0 loss to [[England national under-21 football team|England]] in the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66069220|first=Alex|last=Howell|title=England U21 1–0 Portugal U21|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=2 July 2023|access-date=14 July 2023|archive-date=11 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230711202505/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66069220|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Senior===
On 15 March 2024, Conceição was called to the [[Portugal national football team|senior squad]] by manager [[Roberto Martínez]] for [[Exhibition game#International football|friendlies]] with [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] and [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Jota Silva "muito feliz" com chamada à Seleção: "Era uma coisa que queria há muito tempo"|trans-title=Jota Silva "very happy" with national team callup: "It was something I wanted for a long time"|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/selecoes/detalhe/jota-silva-muito-feliz-com-chamada-a-selecao-era-uma-coisa-que-queria-ha-muito-tempo|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=15 March 2024|access-date=18 March 2024|archive-date=18 March 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240318144603/https://www.record.pt/futebol/selecoes/detalhe/jota-silva-muito-feliz-com-chamada-a-selecao-era-uma-coisa-que-queria-ha-muito-tempo|url-status=live}}</ref> He debuted on 26 March in a friendly match against the latter that ended in a 2–0 loss.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Cristina|last=Aguiar|title=Francisco Conceição estreou-se na Seleção: "Não estive ao melhor nível"|trans-title=Francisco Conceição debuted in the national team: "I wasn't at the best level"|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/219392885/francisco-conceicao-estreou-se-na-selecao-nao-estive-ao-melhor-nivel/|website=[[O Jogo]]|date=26 March 2024|access-date=30 May 2024|language=pt|archive-date=20 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620234431/https://www.ojogo.pt/219392885/francisco-conceicao-estreou-se-na-selecao-nao-estive-ao-melhor-nivel/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 21 May, he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=21 May 2024 |title=Convocados para o Euro 2024 |trans-title=Called up for Euro 2024 |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-not%C3%ADcias/Not%C3%ADcia/news/45104 |publisher=[[Portuguese Football Federation]] |access-date=21 May 2024 |language=pt |archive-date=21 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240521123759/https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-not%C3%ADcias/Not%C3%ADcia/news/45104 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 18 June, he came off the bench in the 90th minute, before scoring his first goal for Portugal two minutes later, which secured a 2–1 victory over the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]] in the opening match.<ref>{{cite web|title=Francisco Conceição: Roberto Martínez Full of Praise for Portugal Matchwinner: "He has a scent for danger"|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/euro/2024/francisco-conceicao-roberto-martinez-full-of-praise-for-portugal-match-winner-he-has-a-scent-for-danger_sto20011894/story.shtml|website=[[Eurosport]]|date=19 June 2024|access-date=19 June 2024|archive-date=18 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240618230722/https://www.eurosport.com/football/euro/2024/francisco-conceicao-roberto-martinez-full-of-praise-for-portugal-match-winner-he-has-a-scent-for-danger_sto20011894/story.shtml|url-status=live}}</ref> His father [[Sérgio Conceição|Sérgio]] had scored a hat-trick against [[Germany national football team|Germany]] almost exactly 24 years earlier on 20 June 2000 during [[UEFA Euro 2000]];<ref>{{cite web |title=History: Portugal 3–0 Germany |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/match/64850/ |website=UEFA |access-date=19 June 2024 |archive-date=18 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230418221904/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/match/64850/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Fahey |first=Ciarán |date=2024-06-18 |title=Conceição scores in stoppage time to get Portugal off to winning start at Euro 2024 |url=https://apnews.com/article/euro2024-portugal-czech-republic-preview-10fb8ccb9755c7021fefbd849118f383 |access-date=2024-06-19 |website=AP News |language=en |archive-date=20 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620234431/https://apnews.com/article/euro2024-portugal-czech-republic-preview-10fb8ccb9755c7021fefbd849118f383 |url-status=live }}</ref> as such they became the second father and son pair to have scored a goal in a [[UEFA European Championship|European Championship]], after the Italians [[Enrico Chiesa|Enrico]] and [[Federico Chiesa]] who had scored respectively in Euros [[UEFA Euro 1996|1996]] and [[UEFA Euro 2020|2020]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Chiesa makes Euro 2020 history |url=https://football-italia.net/chiesa-makes-euro-2020-history/ |website=Football Italia |date=26 June 2021 |access-date=19 June 2024 |archive-date=2 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210702160135/https://football-italia.net/chiesa-makes-euro-2020-history/ |url-status=live }}</ref> After not featuring against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]], he played the full 90 minutes of the final [[UEFA Euro 2024 Group F|Group F]] fixture against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] which Portugal lost 2–0,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036196--georgia-vs-portugal/|title=Georgia vs Portugal|access-date=3 July 2024|website=UEFA}}</ref> before making two further appearances off the bench against Slovenia (3–0 victory in a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/crgkd32x07zt?page=17|title=Portugal 0–0 Slovenia (Portugal win 3–0 on pens)|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Emma|last=Sanders|date=1 July 2024|access-date=4 July 2024}}</ref> and [[France national football team|France]] in the knockout stage (5–3 loss in another shootout).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy79llev4znt|title=Portugal 0–0 France (France win 5–3 on pens)|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Emma|last=Sanders|date=5 July 2024|access-date=6 July 2024}}</ref>

In May 2025, Conceição was selected for Portugal’s [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals]] [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals squads#Portugal|squad]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Convocatória para Liga das Nações divulgada |trans-title=Nations League squad announced |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-notícias/Notícia/news/50645 |website=[[Portuguese Football Federation]] |language=pt |access-date=26 May 2025 |date=20 May 2025}}</ref> On 4 June, in the [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals|semi-finals]], he came on from the bench and scored the first goal in the 2–1 win against Germany, marking Portugal's first-ever win against them in 24 years and securing qualification to the [[2025 UEFA Nations League final|Nations League final]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cj6rw18xk1yt|title=Germany 1–2 Portugal|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Michael|last=Emons|date=4 June 2025|access-date=9 June 2025}}</ref> He and his team would go on to win the tournament [[2025 UEFA Nations League final|5–3 in a penalty shootout]] over rivals [[Spain national football team|Spain]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6408339/2025/06/08/spain-portugal-yamal-mendes-ronaldo/|title=Spain 2 Portugal 2 (3–5 on pens): Mendes vs Yamal, Ronaldo being Ronaldo, and World Cup chances|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|first1=Tim|last1=Spiers|first2=Dermot|last2=Corrigan|first3=Stu|last3=James|date=8 June 2025|access-date=8 June 2025}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Conceição is a technical winger, with a tight turning radius, outstanding close control and an eye for playmaking in central zones. His game revolves around getting the ball into the penalty area from wide via carries and crosses. His compact build, standing at a low center of gravity coupled with quick, small strides allows him to make frequent and consistent contact with the ball while carrying it. This thereby enables him to execute constant sharp changes of directions. His agile feet also equip him with the ability to swiftly readjust himself to manipulate angles in the box, either to get shots off for himself or to set his teammates up.<ref name="Estilojogo">{{cite web|url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/francisco-conceicao-the-portuguese-winger-stepping-out-of-his-fathers-shadow/|title=Francisco Conceição: The Portuguese Winger Stepping Out of His Father's Shadow|website=Breaking the lines|date=5 July 2024|language=en|accessdate=12 July 2024}}</ref>

Conceição's body composition also gives him good control over his gears, as he utilizes this to square up defenders, to keep them on their toes, before hitting them off guard with a good sudden burst. He also utilizes these short explosive bursts brilliantly when cutting inside, using a variety of touches – long, short, to disrupt the rhythm of defenders.<ref name="Estilojogo"/> His early promise, as well as his small stature (1.70 m),<ref name=minuto>{{cite web|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1695793/francisco-conceicao|title=Há um 'Messi' a nascer no Olival e cada vez mais decisivo no FC Porto|website=Notícias ao Minuto|author=Querido, Rodrigo|date=24 February 2021|language=pt|trans-title=A "Messi" is born at Olival and he is increasingly decisive in FC Porto|accessdate=11 March 2021|archive-date=20 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620234432/https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1695793/francisco-conceicao|url-status=live}}</ref> led to comparisons to [[Eden Hazard]] and [[Lionel Messi]] in the Portuguese press,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/fc-porto/detalhe/francisco-o-filho-de-conceicao-que-nao-tem-nada-a-ver-com-o-pai-e-faz-lembrar-messi|title=Francisco: o filho de Conceição que 'não tem nada a ver com o pai' e 'faz lembrar Messi'|website=Record|date=14 February 2021|language=pt|author=Custódio, Miguel|trans-title=Francisco: Conceição's son that is "nothing like his father" and "reminds of Messi"|accessdate=11 March 2021|archive-date=20 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620234435/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/fc-porto/detalhe/francisco-o-filho-de-conceicao-que-nao-tem-nada-a-ver-com-o-pai-e-faz-lembrar-messi|url-status=live}}</ref> with him sometimes being nicknamed "Messi do Olival" ([[CTFD PortoGaia|Olival]]'s Messi) by fans and in media outlets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jn.pt/desporto/messi-do-olival-cumpre-sonho-e-da-a-vida-pelo-pai-13352798.html|title="Messi do Olival" cumpre sonho e dá a vida pelo pai|website=[[Jornal de Notícias]]|language=pt|date=15 February 2021|author=Martins, Arnaldo|accessdate=11 March 2021|trans-title="Olival's Messi" fulfills his dream and gives his life for his father|archive-date=3 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210303112433/https://www.jn.pt/desporto/messi-do-olival-cumpre-sonho-e-da-a-vida-pelo-pai-13352798.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in Coimbra, Conceição is the fourth son of former [[Portugal national football team|Portugal international]] footballer and Al-Ittihad manager [[Sérgio Conceição]]; his older brothers [[Sérgio Conceição (footballer, born 1996)|Sérgio]] and [[Rodrigo Conceição|Rodrigo]] are also professional footballers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://observador.pt/2017/06/08/o-cla-conceicao-o-pai-treina-o-fc-porto-um-filho-joga-no-benfica-outro-esta-no-sporting/|title=O clã Conceição: o pai treina o FC Porto, um filho joga no Benfica, outro está no Sporting|trans-title=The Conceição family: the father manages FC Porto, a son plays in Benfica and another in Sporting|website=Observador|language=pt|date=8 June 2017|author=Roseiro, Bruno|accessdate=15 February 2021|archive-date=11 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611160649/https://observador.pt/2017/06/08/o-cla-conceicao-o-pai-treina-o-fc-porto-um-filho-joga-no-benfica-outro-esta-no-sporting/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/2019/12/28/futebol-nacional/filho-de-sergio-conceicao-estreia-se-na-ii-liga/noticia/176710/|title=Filho de Sérgio Conceição estreia-se na II Liga|trans-title=Sérgio Conceição's son debuts in II Liga|website=Rádio Renascença|language=pt|date=28 December 2019|author=Soares da Silva, Eduardo|accessdate=16 February 2021|archive-date=29 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191229224747/https://rr.sapo.pt/2019/12/28/futebol-nacional/filho-de-sergio-conceicao-estreia-se-na-ii-liga/noticia/176710/|url-status=live}}</ref>

